{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 23:31:40.508258", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission summary:\n- Is anomaly: true\n- Faulty devices: server_access_router, dns_server, web_server_0, web_server_1, web_server_2, web_server_3\n- Root cause(s): dns_record_error, sender_application_delay\n\nRationale:\n- Policy violation: Back-end web servers are directly reachable from user subnets. This points to missing/misconfigured access control on the server_access_router (prime enforcement point). While “missing ACL” root cause is not explicitly listed, the DNS zone is also exposing backend A records, enabling direct access. Thus dns_record_error is selected to capture DNS exposure.\n- Elevated HTTP time-to-first-byte despite sub-10 ms RTTs is consistent with application-side latency, captured by sender_application_delay.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1960, "output_tokens": 159, "total_tokens": 2119, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1408}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
